# ================================
# XMTP Agent Configuration
# ================================

# Your wallet private key (with 0x prefix)
# Generate: use your existing wallet or create one with: npx @xmtp/cli generate-wallet
XMTP_WALLET_KEY=0x1234567890abcdef1234567890abcdef1234567890abcdef1234567890abcdef

# XMTP Network environment
# Options: 'local', 'dev', 'production'
# Use 'dev' for testing, 'production' for mainnet
XMTP_ENV=production

# Database encryption key (64 hex characters, no 0x prefix)
# Generate: run `npm run generate-credentials`
# IMPORTANT: Keep this secret and backed up! If lost, you lose access to all messages.
XMTP_DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY=a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2

# ================================
# AI Configuration (Claude)
# ================================

# Anthropic API key for Claude
# Get yours at: https://console.anthropic.com/
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-...

# ================================
# Locus MCP Configuration
# ================================

# Locus API Key for MCP server authentication
# Get yours at: https://app.paywithlocus.com/dashboard/agents
# NOTE: Using API key (simpler) instead of OAuth for faster integration
LOCUS_API_KEY=locus_your_api_key_here

# Locus MCP Server URL (optional - defaults to production)
# LOCUS_MCP_SERVER_URL=https://mcp.paywithlocus.com

# ================================
# Railway Configuration (Optional)
# ================================

# Railway automatically sets this when using volumes
# Leave empty for local development
# RAILWAY_VOLUME_MOUNT_PATH=/data

# HTTP server port (Railway sets this automatically)
# PORT=3000

# ================================
# Quick Start Instructions
# ================================

# 1. Create Locus wallet and fund with USDC:
#    https://app.paywithlocus.com/dashboard/wallets
#
# 2. Create Policy Group and approve x402 endpoints:
#    https://app.paywithlocus.com/dashboard/agents
#    - Approve ethyai.app/x402/ta (Locus facilitator)
#    - Approve services from x402scan.com (CDP facilitator)
#
# 3. Create Agent and get API key:
#    https://app.paywithlocus.com/dashboard/agents
#    Copy LOCUS_API_KEY above
#
# 4. Generate XMTP credentials:
#    npm run generate-credentials
#
# 5. Get Anthropic API key:
#    https://console.anthropic.com/
#
# 6. Install dependencies:
#    npm install
#
# 7. Start agent:
#    npm run dev
#
# 8. Test by sending XMTP message to your agent address!

# ================================
# Multi-Facilitator Architecture
# ================================

# Your agent automatically uses BOTH:
# - Locus facilitator (ethyai.app services)
# - CDP facilitator (x402scan marketplace)
#
# Claude decides which services to call based on the user query.
# Locus MCP handles all payments automatically with policy enforcement.

# ================================
# Production Deployment (Railway)
# ================================

# Required environment variables for Railway:
# - XMTP_WALLET_KEY
# - XMTP_ENV=production
# - XMTP_DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY
# - ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
# - LOCUS_API_KEY
# - RAILWAY_VOLUME_MOUNT_PATH (set automatically by Railway)
# - PORT (set automatically by Railway)

# ================================
# Removed Variables (No Longer Needed)
# ================================

# The following are NOT needed with Locus MCP:
# ❌ OPENAI_API_KEY - Using Claude instead
# ❌ PRIVATE_KEY - Locus wallet manages payments
# ❌ PAYMENT_ADDRESS - Not needed for agent
# ❌ BASE_RPC_URL - Locus handles blockchain
# ❌ USE_MAINNET - Locus handles network
# ❌ CDP_API_KEY_ID/SECRET - Locus backend handles
# ❌ MARKET_DATA_SERVICE - Using real x402 endpoints
# ❌ SENTIMENT_SERVICE - Using real x402 endpoints
# ❌ ONCHAIN_SERVICE - Using real x402 endpoints
